page.title: 06ECOLOGY 2
page.content: There are some well cared for nature parks and gardens which provide homes for {swifts, song thrushes, mistle {thrushes, blackbirds, house martins, {blue tits, wrens, chaffinches, robins, and{collared dove.}There are also some very untidy gardens which give homes to the invertebrates that feed the birds but also encourage{brown {rats}and{house mice.}Cats prey on these and the garden birds. There are some large ponds stocked for coarse fishing with{mute swans, moorhens, {coots, mallards, water voles, common {frogs, toads}and{common newts.}A stream runs through the grassland where frogs are also found. We think it likely that {grass snakes}also live here.{Swallows}fly over the water catching insects.
